<div class="compWrap"><span id="Header" class="compTitle">Header <span class="js-hideAll fa fa-eye"></span></span><p class="compNotes">The big text on the top of the whole website should catch the user and make him or her curious about Clockwise. It is centered and its position varies depending on the device you are using. On mobile devices for example the header appears underneath the register form as it is easier for users to have everything right at the first glance when on their phone. However when they are on a computer they are more likely to navigate around so the big header on the top is more of a nice looking component rather than a distraction.<br>This part again builds up on the skeleton css. For more information see <a href="atomic-core/Layout.php#Grid" class="link">Layout</a>.</p><div class="component" style="background-color:"><?php include("../components/LandingPage/Header.php");?></div><div class="compCodeBox"> <ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist"> <li role="presentation" class="active"><a href="#Header-markup" aria-controls="Header-markup" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Markup</a></li><li role="presentation"><a href="#Header-css" aria-controls="Header-css" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">scss</a></li></ul> <div class="tab-content"> <div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active markup-display" id="Header-markup"></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="Header-css"><pre><code class="language-css"><?php include("../scss/LandingPage/_Header.scss");?></code></pre></div></div></div></div>